# Admin UI Design Playbook

When designing or implementing admin UI:

- Clarify style, competitors, users, and core tasks first.
- Avoid generic AI-looking mockups.
- Prefer professional business layouts over decorative card-heavy pages.
- Use clear navigation, structured content regions, readable filters, and operationally useful tables.
- Avoid large titles and long descriptive text unless the product genuinely needs them.
